$ Oracle: Users and roles

→ development/databases/Oracle/users-roles/users[Users] and roles have in common that both of them can be granted
→ development/databases/Oracle/security/privileges[privileges] and (kind of recursively) roles.
-
Because of this similarity, it comes as no surprise that both, users and roles, are listed in the base table
`→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/base-tables/user`.


sa:

  User *SYS* is created in → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/rdbms/admin/dsec_bsq[`$ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/admin/dsec.bsq`]
